@startuml folio-sequence-submit-to-journal
' Folio — Author submits manuscript (UC-01)
' Matches: POST /api/v1/submissions/:slug/submit, transactional outbox, submission.submitted
' Render: https://www.plantuml.com/plantuml

title Submit to journal (UC-01)

actor Author
participant "Folio UI\n(Next.js)" as UI
participant "Backend API\n(NestJS)" as API
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
queue "RabbitMQ" as MQ
participant "Email service" as Email
participant "SMTP" as SMTP

Author -> UI : Open submission,\nconfirm metadata/files
Author -> UI : Tap **Submit**
UI -> API : POST /submissions/:slug/submit\n(JWT)

API -> API : Validate author,\nstatus = draft/revisions,\nfiles & constructor rules

alt Validation fails
  API --> UI : 400 validation error
  UI --> Author : Show error;\nstays draft
else Success
  API -> DB : BEGIN transaction
  API -> DB : UPDATE submission\nstatus = **submitted**
  API -> DB : INSERT outbox rows\n(submission.submitted per editor/JM)
  API -> DB : INSERT in-app notifications
  API -> DB : COMMIT

  API -> MQ : Publish outbox events\n(after commit)
  API --> UI : 200 submission (submitted)
  UI --> Author : Success

  MQ -> Email : Consume submission.submitted
  Email -> Email : Render template\n(idempotent)
  Email -> SMTP : Send mail to each\neditor / journal manager
  SMTP --> Email : OK
end

@enduml
